{"id": 530, "date": "2018-01-31T05:00:03", "date_gmt": "2018-01-31T13:00:03", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=530"}, "modified": "2021-04-10T11:50:24", "modified_gmt": "2021-04-10T18:50:24", "slug": "cover-me-robert-gordon-and-link-wray-fire", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/01/31/cover-me-robert-gordon-and-link-wray-fire/", "title": {"rendered": "Cover Me, Robert Gordon and Link Wray: Fire"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Robert Gordon and Link Wray were the first to record and release Bruce Springsteen&#8217;s &#8220;<a href=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/08/05/roll-of-the-dice-fire/\">Fire</a>.&#8221; Bruce gave Gordon the song after seeing him perform with Wray; they released it in 1978, years before Bruce&#8217;s version debuted on\u00a0<em>Live 1975-1985</em>, and decades before the Bruce&#8217;s studio version surfaced on\u00a0<em>The Promise.</em></p>\n<p>This recording from a BBC studio session very well be the definitive take on the song&#8211;just listen to Link Wray go to town on it.</p>\n<div id=\"v-gTYrUMsj-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='504' src='https://videopress.com/embed/gTYrUMsj?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p>Bonus: Here&#8217;s the original 1978 recording (with Bruce Springsteen on piano) for comparison.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Fire\" width=\"758\" height=\"569\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rQJaMpXH0X0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"acceleromet